'''Daniel 'Dani' Ponce de Le<U+00F3>n Garc<U+00ED>a''' (born 16 May 1991) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[<U+00DA>jpest FC]] in Hungary, on loan from [[AD Alcorc<U+00F3>n]], as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].

==Football career==
A product of [[AD Torrej<U+00F3>n CF]]'s youth system, Ponce made his senior debuts in the [[2010<U+2013>11 Tercera Divisi<U+00F3>n|2010<U+2013>11 season]] with [[Real <U+00C1>vila CF]], in the [[Tercera Divisi<U+00F3>n|fourth division]]. He continued to compete in the fourth level in the following seasons, representing [[CD Coslada]] and [[AD Alcorc<U+00F3>n B]].

On 20 October 2013 Ponce made his first appearance with the [[AD Alcorc<U+00F3>n|main squad]], playing the last 3 minutes in a 0<U+2013>1 away loss against [[Real Ja<U+00E9>n]].<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2013/10/20/futbol/2adivision/1382288911.html Jona aprieta la zona de abajo (Jona puts pressure on relegation zone)]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 20 October 2013 {{es icon}}</ref> He appeared in further five matches during [[2013<U+2013>14 Segunda Divisi<U+00F3>n|the campaign]], and renewed his link with the [[Madrid]] side for three years on 11 July of the following year, being also definitely promoted to the first team.<ref>[http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2014/07/11/segunda/1405099510_248909.html Dani Ponce renueva tres temporadas con el Alcorc<U+00F3>n (Dani Ponce renews for three seasons with Alcorc<U+00F3>n)]; [[Diario AS]], 11 July 2014 {{es icon}}</ref>

On 16 August 2014 Ponce was loaned to Hungrian [[Nemzeti Bajnoks<U+00E1>g I]] side [[<U+00DA>jpest FC]].<ref>[http://adalcorcon.com/dani-ponce-cedido-al-ujpest-fc/ Dani Ponce cedido al <U+00D9>jpest FC (Dani Ponce loaned to <U+00DA>jpest FC)]; Alcorc<U+00F3>n's official website, 16 August 2014 {{es icon}}</ref>

